FBIS4-63124 "drsov098__a94025" FBIS-SOV-94-098-A Daily Report 20 May 1994 ANNEX Russia National Affairs Peacekeepers Fired Upon in Ossetia-Ingushetia Peacekeepers Fired Upon in Ossetia-Ingushetia LD2005105194 Moscow RIA in English 0935 GMT 20 May 94--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY LD2005105194 Moscow RIA English BFN [Text] Vladikavkaz, May 20, RIA -- Russian peacekeeping troops came under fire on two occasions in the state of emergency zone in North Ossetia and Ingushetia last night. In the area of the village Nizhny Batakayurt in North Ossetia an armoured personnel carrier was shot at from the Niva car driving by. In another incident a post of Russian Interior Ministry troops in Ingushetia came under fire from the direction of the village Dolakovo at 2 a.m.. According to the press centre of the provisional administration of the zone under state of emergency, in both incidents Russian troops returned fire. No deaths or injuries resulting from the shooting were reported.
